					<description><![CDATA[I had a chance to talk to Rolf downtown at the Cook County Police Department and these are my findings. Me: Name? Rolf: Rolf. Me: Age? Rolf: Dog years or people years? Me: Does it matter? Rolf: Yes. Me: Okay, people years. Rolf: I’m not&#160;<a class="read-more" href="https://llgt.cafe/questioning-rolf-at-chicago-pd">&#8230;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>I had a chance to talk to Rolf downtown at the Cook County Police Department and these are my findings.</p>



<p>Me: Name?</p>



<p>Rolf: Rolf.</p>



<p>Me: Age?</p>



<p>Rolf: Dog years or people years?</p>



<p>Me: Does it matter?</p>



<p>Rolf: Yes.</p>



<p>Me: Okay, people years.</p>



<p>Rolf: I’m not sure, I was pretty young when I was born, and I lost my birth certificate.</p>



<p>Me: Where were you between the hours of 8 and 9 pm last Friday.</p>



<p>Rolf: At the bar — doing comedy. It doesn’t pay well right now, but I expect to be mediocre some day. Maybe even slightly funny.</p>



<p>Me: Do you have any witnesses to collaborate your story?</p>



<p>Rolf: I’m not sure. I think everyone fell asleep after the first minute of my act. The bartender may have been able to stay awake.</p>



<p>Me: So, Rolf, tell me about yourself. What do you like to do in your free time?</p>



<p>Rolf: Short walks on a long leash.</p>



<p>Me: Where do you like to spend most of your time?</p>



<p>Rolf: In bed.</p>



<p>Me: Other than that?</p>



<p>Rolf: At the dog park.</p>



<p>Me: And what do you do there?</p>



<p>Rolf: I like to check out the girl dogs. You know, do the sniff test. Anyway…</p>



<p>Me: Do you talk to these girl dogs</p>



<p>Rolf: I try to and I’m not shy. I just don’t think they understand me or my sense of humor. I graduated from college, after all. You know, I paid a guy in a dark alley $1,200 for my diploma form Harvard.</p>



<p>Me: Did you actually take any classes?</p>



<p>Rolf: No, why?</p>



<p>Me: What is your favorite food?</p>



<p>Rolf: Cat. No, seriously, I like just about everything — Italian, American, Indian, Hawaiian, Mexican…. I’ve studied British foods but I find most of them to be too bland. And cow tongue, I won’t touch it.</p>



<p>Me: Favorite music.</p>



<p>Rolf: I love <a href="https://amzn.to/3k4mLWQ" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Audrey Assad</a>. At least her music. I don’t think she would go for a dog like myself. I love it all — some more than others. It’s like a drug to me. I’m addicted. Seriously.</p>



<p>Me: Drugs? Are drug a problem.</p>



<p>Rolf: Yes. My owner drug me to the opera last Saturday. I kept waiting for the fat lady to sing, but there were none.</p>



<p>Me: What do you drink at the bar?</p>



<p>Rolf: Water, unless I they serve a good chai tea. Do you know how hard it is to find a real good chai tea?</p>



<p>Me: No.</p>



<p>Rolf: I found one place near the University of Arkansas but they want almost $6 for a small cup. A good cup of cappuccino is nearly impossible to find and I’m not going to Italy any time soon.</p>



<p>Me: Speaking of going anywhere, maybe you should plan to stay in town for the next week or two.</p>



<p>Rolf: I plan to. I have shows to preform this Saturday and the next. Besides, I just walked form Vegas where my Pa and Grandpa live and, boy, are my Pas tired.</p>



<p>Me: Do you have any tickets?</p>



<p>Rolf: For you? No. It’s first come first serve. Ten dollar minimum.</p>



<p>Me: Okay, Rolf, you’re free to go — for now. You’ve been very funny — I mean “informative”.</p>



<p>Rolf: Thank you, thank you very muuuch. No, wait. If you have extra dog food, make sure you share it with others who are in need. There are a lot of hungry dogs out there. And make sure you share the love. Don’t keep it to yourself.</p>



<p>Me: Ladies and gentlemen — Rolf the Dawg.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
